Spring Core and Maven – Cognizant Interview Notes


1. What is Spring Framework?

Spring Framework is an open-source Java framework used for building enterprise-level applications. 
It simplifies Java development by providing features like Dependency Injection (DI), Aspect-Oriented Programming (AOP), transaction management, 
MVC architecture, security, and database integration.

Definition

Spring is a lightweight, loosely coupled, and modular framework that makes Java application development easier.

Why was Spring introduced?

Before Spring, Java developers mainly used EJB (Enterprise JavaBeans).

Problems with EJB:

Complex configuration
Heavyweight
Difficult testing
Tight coupling
Requires application server

Spring solved these by providing

Lightweight framework
POJO programming
Dependency Injection
Easy testing
Modular architecture
